<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-02-20T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-02-20T15:00:00-05:00" n="435" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d435">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/4321: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul at Geneva (<persName corresp="#p_GPB1" type="to">Gilbert</persName>)</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-20T15:00:00-05:00">February 20, 1932—3
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>40. Your 86, February 19, 10 p.m. Inform <persName corresp="#p_DSE1">Drummond</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_PBJ1">Boncour</persName> that this Government is in entire sympathy with
                            the endeavor of the Council to have the time limit of the ultimatum
                            extended but that, as hostilities have now begun it would be useless for
                            this Government to take similar action.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_SHL1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>